	<article id="post-1191" class="post-1191 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized tag-android tag-android-4-4 tag-cupcake tag-great-read tag-kitkat">
				<header class="entry-header">
									<h1 class="entry-title">
				<a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/1191/androids-history" rel="bookmark">The history of Android</a>
			</h1>
										<div class="comments-link">
					<a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/1191/androids-history#respond" title="Comment on The history of Android"><span class="dsq-postid" rel="1191 http://envyandroid.com/?p=1191"><span class="leave-reply">Leave a reply</span></span></a>				</div><!-- .comments-link -->
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p>Ron Amadeo of the tech news site Ars Technica, recently posted a rather lengthy article on Android history, from version 0.5 to todays 4.4. Its worth reading.</p>
<p><a href="http://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2014/06/building-android-a-40000-word-history-of-googles-mobile-os/1/">The history of Android</a></p>
<p>I now notice that android has come a looong way, since my first android device, the white HTC Magic with cupcake 1.5, to the Nexus 5 with android 4.4.3.</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t think I could ever go back to the magic, today.<br />
(I shiver when I see one of my friends still using it.)</p>
<div class='shareaholic-canvas' data-app-id='7003085' data-app='share_buttons' data-title='The history of Android' data-link='http://envyandroid.com/archives/1191/androids-history' data-summary=''></div>					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
		<footer class="entry-meta">
			This entry was posted in <a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/category/uncategorized" title="View all posts in Uncategorized" rel="category tag">Uncategorized</a> and tagged <a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/tag/android" rel="tag">Android</a>, <a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/tag/android-4-4" rel="tag">Android 4.4</a>, <a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/tag/cupcake" rel="tag">Cupcake</a>, <a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/tag/great-read" rel="tag">Great read</a>, <a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/tag/kitkat" rel="tag">KitKat</a> on <a href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/1191/androids-history" title="19:12" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2014-06-18T19:12:28+00:00">June 18, 2014</time></a><span class="by-author"> by <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://envyandroid.com/archives/author/admin" title="View all posts by EnvyAndroid" rel="author">EnvyAndroid</a></span></span>.								</footer><!-- .entry-meta -->
